The error also happens for non-array properties. So it's a more general issue with possibly undefined form properties.
See [this example](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play?ts=4.7.4#code/KYDwDg9gTgLgBAE2AYwDYEMrDjAnmbAWWCgHNgAeAQQBo4AhAPjgF44BvAKDh7gG0A0nACWAOzgBrYLggAzOFTgAfSdLkMAugH4AXHCGgYwUQgDOqmfMVb9cQ8bMX19ODb5VBGuvU8a7IIxNzPggAIwArFBg6MMjkGD8bYjJKDwEvBk9mPTS-FR90uBzPItt7IKd5FxsCvz1RYAA3EgBuTgBfNtBIWEQUDCwcfGwAMWFgVAQANXRUAFdgczYAJRRoBApTGCgxUjp0UVxGLvBoeCQ0TGw8AjgxiYQAUSgoaFYObl4AW0XTdHJdHAtjtRKQ2p1ON0zn1LoMbqNxpNnq8oKYKAAVfyBRz3SYzeaLd646azBamZhsLi8fhCMSVODo7R6dElcqOWJRVxwZLkCjE5HQOj8l7QNEs9KMbJ3RFPEVQcFtTiceHc3DE-Fk95U3iyCAQQHa6k8UKYPTA3afHgQ9pK5AQURbOAACwOCFQwAFqPeAAoSCjTHphf6KIQ1TKNYtGABKVjMQ1wO0OiDugB0fugvrlphTuv1KZNUC0KZ+pj+5CjHU4icdLpM7s9pgAwtAsPFULgfenUYGZQ2Q2GHhHyTGWHHLQn7aZk8A03LvZn-Tm9XB0OYg6KKOw4AWzdtdnB2tGiwWiyWy8AK+0gA).

```ts
type MyFieldValues = {
    foo?: {
        bar: string
    };
}

const handleErrors = (errors: FieldErrors<MyFieldValues>) => {
    console.error(errors.foo?.bar?.message)
}
```

Causes this error:
```bash
Property 'bar' does not exist on type 'FieldError'.
```

And the hotfix is again a user-defined type guard:
```ts
const handleErrorsCorrectly = (errors: FieldErrors<MyFieldValues>) => {
    console.error((errors.foo as FieldErrors<{ bar: string }>)?.bar?.message)
}
```

